SUMMARY:Boot process for modern Linux
DESCRIPTION: In the latest iterations of Linux, many features have been added regarding the Boot Process, including a new standard called BLS with support in GRUB2 and systemd-boot, Full Disk Encryption using TPM, and having the entire boot process signed, ensuring system integrity.\n\nAnother interesting feature is soft-reboot, which is the ability to reboot the entire userspace, without rebooting the hardware or reloading the kernel like kexec does. In this talk we will talk about these features, and why the major actors are collaborating on them.
